This paper proposes a method for support vector machine classification, which is a common topic in machine learning (cs.LG). The method involves computing a proxy kernel matrix, which is a numerical optimization problem that can be solved using numerical analysis techniques (cs.NA). The paper also mentions comparing the performance of their technique with other methods on classic data sets, which suggests that the paper may fall under computer vision (cs.CV), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), or data structures and algorithms (cs.DS) sub-categories.
